"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448601","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-02-03","<p>Broadcasting Support Services (BSS) was contracted in 2009 to run the Pay and Work Rights Helpline (PWRH) until March 2015.</p><p> </p><p>In April 2015 Acas took over responsibility for providing a one stop shop for workers and employers seeking advice on a wider range of employment matters.</p><p> </p><p>The budget was: 2009/10 - £968k, with 9 members of staff; and in 2014/15 it was £750k, with 7 members of staff. The cost of the service was then absorbed by Acas within their existing helpline functions when they took over responsibility for handling calls previously dealt with by the PWRH.</p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2016-02-03T17:02:26.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448601/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448601/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448601/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2016-01-28","Revenue and Customs: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many full-time equivalent staff were employed by HM Revenue and Customs' Pay and Work Rights Helpline in (a) 2009-10, (b) 2014-15 and (c) 2015-16; and what funding was provided to that team in each of those years.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","24860"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448602","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-03","<p>The government does not publish projected growth forecasts for individual regions of the country. However, last year we published our Long Term Economic Plan for Yorkshire and Northern Lincolnshire where we detailed our ambition for the region to achieve a long term growth rate to at least that of the whole of the UK. This would increase the size of the Yorkshire and Northern Lincolnshire economies by an extra £13 billion in real terms by 2030, equivalent to over £2,000 per person.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-02-03T16:09:26.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448602/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448602/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448602/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-28","Economic Growth: Yorkshire and the Humber","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the projected growth of the economy in Yorkshire and Humber over the course of this Parliament.","false","Biography information for Craig Whittaker","Calder Valley","Craig Whittaker","24658"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448603","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-03","<p>This is a matter for the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA), which is operationally independent from Government.</p><p> </p><p>The question has been passed on to the FCA. The FCA will reply directly to the Rt Hon Joan Ryan MP by letter. A copy of the letter will be placed in the Library of the House.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","24719 ; 24720 ; 24721 ; 24722","2016-02-03T16:13:41.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448603/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448603/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448603/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-28","Financial Institutions: Databases","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent assessment the Financial Conduct Authority has made of the effectiveness of its regulations to ensure record keeping by banks and other financial institutions are not being (a) deleted, (b) manipulated or (c) altered.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","24718"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448604","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-03","<p>This is a matter for the Financial Conduct Authority (FCA), which is operationally independent from Government.</p><p> </p><p>The question has been passed on to the FCA. The FCA will reply directly to the Rt Hon Joan Ryan MP by letter. A copy of the letter will be placed in the Library of the House.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","24718 ; 24720 ; 24721 ; 24722","2016-02-03T16:13:41.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448604/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448604/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448604/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-28","Banks: Databases","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what consideration the Financial Conduct Authority has given to requests from banks to sign a memorandum of understanding to ensure that financial record keeping regulations in the UK are not being breached.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","24719"
